♪ And now it's filled
with Jesus ♪
♪ <i>It's filled with Jesus</i> ♪

12:33.987 --> 12:35.954
♪ There was a hole
♪ <i>Was a hole</i> ♪

12:35.956 --> 12:37.922
♪ In my wife
♪ <i>Hole in wife</i> ♪

12:37.924 --> 12:41.025
♪ Her hole's filled
with Jesus, too ♪

12:41.027 --> 12:42.927
♪ <i>That came out wrong</i> ♪

12:42.929 --> 12:47.499
♪ My cup is filled
by my redeemer ♪

12:47.501 --> 12:51.169
♪ I'm the coffee,
he's the creamer ♪

12:51.171 --> 12:55.006
ALL:
♪ Worship him or he'll
damn you all to Hell! ♪

12:55.008 --> 12:56.641
Whoo, praise the Lord!

12:56.643 --> 12:59.210
You know, the Bible says that
when two or more are gathered

12:59.212 --> 13:02.113
in his name,
he will be there, too,

13:02.115 --> 13:03.948
and I can feel him here tonight!

13:03.950 --> 13:04.649
Amen.

13:04.651 --> 13:05.950
You listening, Junior?

13:05.952 --> 13:09.654
He is here in this room,
and he wants you to know

13:09.656 --> 13:12.023
he can work miracles
in your life.

13:12.025 --> 13:16.094
♪ He raised the dead,
he healed the lame ♪

13:16.096 --> 13:20.098
♪ He helped me win
my T-ball game ♪

13:20.100 --> 13:24.035
♪ He turned water into wine

13:24.037 --> 13:28.273
♪ Not Boone's Farm,
the fancy kind ♪

13:28.275 --> 13:30.842
♪ Worship him or he'll
damn you all to Hell! ♪

13:30.844 --> 13:33.511
Whoo, I'm gonna dance now
'cause I ain't a Baptist.

13:33.513 --> 13:34.779
♪ There was a hole

13:34.781 --> 13:35.780
♪ <i>Was a hole</i> ♪

13:35.782 --> 13:36.781
♪ In my life

13:36.783 --> 13:38.049
♪ <i>In his life</i> ♪

13:38.051 --> 13:40.318
♪ And now it's filled
with Jesus ♪

13:40.320 --> 13:41.886
♪ <i>It's filled with Christ</i> ♪

13:43.689 --> 13:45.490
♪ The coolest guy
from Bethlehem ♪

13:45.492 --> 13:47.091
♪ Misunderstood like Eminem

13:47.093 --> 13:49.027
♪ His throne sits
past the pearly gates ♪

13:49.029 --> 13:51.362
♪ I pray to him
when I'm two weeks late... ♪

13:51.364 --> 13:52.664
(music stops)
With a term paper.

13:52.666 --> 13:53.965
(music resumes)

13:53.967 --> 13:58.002
♪ If you're stuck with kids
that act like pills ♪

13:58.004 --> 14:02.006
♪ He finds a man
to pay your bills ♪

14:02.008 --> 14:06.144
♪ He loves you,
but he will damn you to ♪

14:06.146 --> 14:10.849
♪ He loves you, but he will
damn you to ♪

14:10.851 --> 14:12.951
♪ He loves you, but He will

14:12.953 --> 14:16.421
♪ Damn you to Hell...

14:16.423 --> 14:18.323
♪ Damn you all to Hell!

14:18.325 --> 14:20.391
(all panting)

14:24.263 --> 14:26.531
Yay!

14:26.533 --> 14:28.600
But... no.

14:32.104 --> 14:34.105
What were we thinking,

14:34.107 --> 14:37.809
doing a huge production number
with no food in the house?

14:37.811 --> 14:40.044
Stupid, stupid.

14:40.046 --> 14:42.113
I'm so hungry.

14:43.549 --> 14:45.550
Ugh, oh, that's nasty.

14:45.552 --> 14:46.517
(spits)

14:46.519 --> 14:48.586
(groaning)

14:51.957 --> 14:53.958
Dumb fern.

14:53.960 --> 14:55.093
Don't eat that.

14:55.095 --> 14:56.828
Hey, Momma,
I know I've been

14:56.830 --> 14:58.963
off the boob
for a few years now,

14:58.965 --> 15:01.499
but you think maybe you could
work up a little something

15:01.501 --> 15:02.934
for old time's sake?

15:02.936 --> 15:05.837
I'm sorry, baby, but these
are just for show now.

15:05.839 --> 15:07.772
The only thing they
produce is stares

15:07.774 --> 15:09.474
from Asian men
at the bank.

15:09.476 --> 15:11.009
We're going to starve to death.

15:11.011 --> 15:12.277
(sobbing)

15:12.279 --> 15:14.812
Hey, where's Junior,

15:14.814 --> 15:17.448
and why isn't he in here trying
to eat one of us?

15:17.450 --> 15:19.484
I bet he's hiding
food in his room.

15:19.486 --> 15:20.785
Of course.

15:20.787 --> 15:23.621
Now, maybe this is just
the severe hunger talking,

15:23.623 --> 15:26.491
but let's get
that bloated son of a bitch

15:26.493 --> 15:28.092
and rip his arms off!

15:28.094 --> 15:31.029
(all screaming)

15:31.031 --> 15:32.797
(gasping)

15:32.799 --> 15:36.334
Junior, how could you hoard food
from your own family?!

15:36.336 --> 15:37.602
What?

15:37.604 --> 15:38.937
I'm not hoarding food.

15:38.939 --> 15:40.171
I'm rationing it.

15:40.173 --> 15:42.040
I don't know the difference!

15:42.042 --> 15:43.942
Look, I knew
the storm was coming

15:43.944 --> 15:45.710
because I'm the only one
in the house

15:45.712 --> 15:49.981
who pays attention to the news,
so I stocked up on essentials.

15:49.983 --> 15:53.017
I took everyone's BMI
and daily caloric intake

15:53.019 --> 15:56.988
and rationed enough food for
each of us to eat for four days.

15:56.990 --> 15:57.956
Nerd.

15:57.958 --> 15:59.791
I care about
you, okay,

15:59.793 --> 16:03.027
and you come in here and
accuse me of hoarding?

16:04.964 --> 16:06.631
You know what?

16:06.633 --> 16:07.865
If you're so hungry,

16:07.867 --> 16:10.501
why don't you just pray
for some damn food?

16:10.503 --> 16:11.502
(all gasp)

16:11.504 --> 16:12.937
How dare you
mock the Lord

16:12.939 --> 16:15.807
in the middle of a natural
disaster he created!

16:15.809 --> 16:19.043
And then deny food
to your starving family!

16:19.045 --> 16:21.179
(thunderclap)
You betrayed us,
Junior.

16:21.181 --> 16:26.150
May God bring his wrath
upon thee!

16:26.152 --> 16:27.652
(thunder booming)

16:31.957 --> 16:32.991
(wind gusting)

16:32.993 --> 16:36.794
(grunting and sputtering)

16:36.796 --> 16:38.663
He's being waterboarded
by nature.

16:38.665 --> 16:39.931
What do we do?

16:39.933 --> 16:43.034
(straining):
I-I can't get him out.

16:43.036 --> 16:45.003
The tree's too heavy.

16:45.005 --> 16:47.038
(à la Walter Cronkite):
And that's the way it is.

16:47.040 --> 16:51.542
Friday, May 19, 1978.

16:51.544 --> 16:52.810
Oh, no.

16:52.812 --> 16:55.113
He thinks
he's Walter Cronkite again.

16:55.115 --> 16:57.815
Man, that's some CBS.

16:57.817 --> 17:02.086
From Dallas, Texas, the flash,
apparently official:

17:02.088 --> 17:05.423
President
Edmond Fitzgerald Kennedy died

17:05.425 --> 17:09.127
at 1:00 p.m.
Central Standard Time.

17:09.129 --> 17:12.964
Two o'clock, three o'clock,
four o'clock rock.

17:12.966 --> 17:14.298
<i>Happy Days.</i>

17:14.300 --> 17:17.769
Sunday, Monday, Tom Bosley.

17:17.771 --> 17:19.270
(thunder cracks)

17:19.272 --> 17:20.972
What are you doing?

17:20.974 --> 17:23.007
My phone's not working
'cause of the storm,

17:23.009 --> 17:25.076
so I'm journaling
my tweets.

17:26.011 --> 17:27.478
Everyone, grab onto the tree

17:27.480 --> 17:29.113
and see if we can lift it.

17:29.115 --> 17:30.815
Not you, Junior.

17:30.817 --> 17:32.550
Yeah, step back,
heathen.

17:32.552 --> 17:35.119
But...
But nothing. This is your fault.

17:35.121 --> 17:36.120
My fault?

17:36.122 --> 17:37.121
How is it my fault?

17:37.123 --> 17:39.791
You got some bad mojo
going on, brother.

17:39.793 --> 17:42.360
This is what you get
when you make God mad.

17:42.362 --> 17:44.962
No, this is what you get
when you ignore the warnings

17:44.964 --> 17:47.665
of the National Weather
Service like a dumbass

17:47.667 --> 17:50.034
and think you can
ride out a hurricane!

17:50.036 --> 17:54.038
And so Vietnam
and hippies and Watergate

17:54.040 --> 17:56.874
and braless low hangers.

17:56.876 --> 17:59.043
Just back off, Junior.

18:00.045 --> 18:02.046
(thunder rumbling)

18:02.048 --> 18:04.449
(playing "Camptown Races")

18:04.451 --> 18:05.817
One more time.

18:05.819 --> 18:09.120
♪ The camptown ladies sing
this song ♪

18:09.122 --> 18:11.456
♪ Doo-dah, doo-dah

18:11.458 --> 18:13.424
♪ The camptown racetrack's
five miles... ♪

18:13.426 --> 18:14.692
(in normal voice):
There I am.

18:14.694 --> 18:16.127
Thank you.

18:16.129 --> 18:18.129
Junior, my boy.

18:18.131 --> 18:19.464
Come here, son.

18:19.466 --> 18:20.698
He sounds bad.

18:20.700 --> 18:22.266
How are we going
to get him out?

18:22.268 --> 18:24.669
We've done everything
we can, Junior.

18:24.671 --> 18:27.038
We're just going to have
to put it in God's hands.

18:27.040 --> 18:29.640
That's a pretty good idea
because God is doing

18:29.642 --> 18:33.678
such a great job with the whole
world right now, sarc mark.

18:33.680 --> 18:35.546
Damn it, Junior, stop it!

18:35.548 --> 18:39.217
I know it might not make sense,
but that's what faith is:

18:39.219 --> 18:41.018
standing in the face
of adversity

18:41.020 --> 18:43.955
and believing that everything's
going to be okay.

18:43.957 --> 18:45.790
Well, excuse me
for not believing

18:45.792 --> 18:49.093
in things you can't
touch, see, or measure.

18:49.095 --> 18:51.963
Junior, Han Solo didn't
believe in the Force,

18:51.965 --> 18:54.031
but he didn't think
Luke Skywalker was

18:54.033 --> 18:55.600
an idiot
for believing in it.

18:55.602 --> 18:56.667
But the Force...

18:56.669 --> 18:58.603
Is what, an unseen presence

18:58.605 --> 19:01.139
from which one draws
strength and inspiration?

19:01.141 --> 19:04.208
How is that any different
from what I'm talking about?

19:05.944 --> 19:08.846
You just blew my mind,
Miss Donna.

19:08.848 --> 19:10.314
Life is hard, Junior,

19:10.316 --> 19:12.150
and when reason
and logic run out,

19:12.152 --> 19:14.252
all you have left
is faith.

19:14.254 --> 19:16.120
Believing that something
greater than myself

19:16.122 --> 19:17.255
is watching
over my family

19:17.257 --> 19:19.357
gets me
through the rough patches.

19:19.359 --> 19:21.092
It gives me peace.

19:21.094 --> 19:23.494
Why would I choose
not to believe that?

19:23.496 --> 19:24.629
(branch cracking)

19:24.631 --> 19:25.763
Cleveland!

19:25.765 --> 19:26.998
Aah, ant on the branch!

19:27.000 --> 19:28.533
There's an ant on the branch!

19:28.535 --> 19:29.800
He's red!

19:29.802 --> 19:31.035
(frantic blowing)

19:35.707 --> 19:37.542
Hey, Lord,
how you doing?

19:37.544 --> 19:39.310
Some weather, huh?

19:39.312 --> 19:42.380
I know Cleveland and I don't
always get along, but he's...

19:42.382 --> 19:43.981
Hey, my Frisbee--
it's in the tree.

19:43.983 --> 19:45.816
I got my Frisbee back.

19:45.818 --> 19:46.918
Thanks, God.

19:46.920 --> 19:47.919
Perfect.

19:47.921 --> 19:49.287
Now maybe
without the extra weight

19:49.289 --> 19:51.355
of that Frisbee, I can do this.

19:51.357 --> 19:54.759
(straining)

19:54.761 --> 19:56.294
Aah, hernia!

19:56.296 --> 19:59.697
And Lord, I ask again
that you hear our prayers,

19:59.699 --> 20:01.599
and if it be your will...

20:01.601 --> 20:02.600
(gasps)

20:02.602 --> 20:03.801
Mama, did you see that?

20:03.803 --> 20:04.969
The tree moved.

20:04.971 --> 20:06.837
God heard
our prayers.

20:06.839 --> 20:09.640
(grunting)

20:09.642 --> 20:12.510
Junior.

20:12.512 --> 20:15.513
Daddy, I'm so
glad you're okay.

20:15.515 --> 20:16.814
If you died,
I don't think

20:16.816 --> 20:18.516
they'd let me live
here anymore.

20:18.518 --> 20:20.017
Probably not.

20:20.019 --> 20:21.786
Junior, I know
it's been a rough day

20:21.788 --> 20:23.187
and I don't want
to embarrass you,

20:23.189 --> 20:26.791
but once again, as with
everything else in your life,

20:26.793 --> 20:29.460
God has made you look
like a fool.

20:29.462 --> 20:30.261
Huh?

20:30.263 --> 20:31.963
God answered our prayers

20:31.965 --> 20:34.532
and got Cleveland out
from under the tree.

20:34.534 --> 20:36.133
But...
Don't you see, son?

20:36.135 --> 20:37.168
God does exist.

20:37.170 --> 20:39.303
He was here tonight
in this room.

20:39.305 --> 20:41.339
You just witnessed
a miracle.

20:41.341 --> 20:43.441
Well, not really.

20:43.443 --> 20:45.843
It was science,
basic engineering.

20:45.845 --> 20:46.944
I did it.

20:46.946 --> 20:50.648
But God showed you
how to build that contraption.

20:50.650 --> 20:51.949
No, I learned that in school.

20:51.951 --> 20:53.751
God built the school.

20:53.753 --> 20:55.353
Immigrants built the school.

20:55.355 --> 20:56.988
Christian immigrants.

20:56.990 --> 20:58.422
I'm out.

20:59.358 --> 21:00.358
(groans)

21:00.360 --> 21:01.459
(sneezes)

21:01.461 --> 21:02.660
God bless you.
